text: A viral Facebook post claims President Donald Trump tweeted in 2009 that he would never let thousands of Americans die from a pandemic while in office.

U.S. President Donald Trump tweeted in November 2009 that Obama's handling of this whole pandemic has been terrible! and that he would never let thousands of Americans die from a pandemic while in office.

In November 2009, Donald Trump tweeted: Obama's handling of this whole pandemic has been terrible! As President, ALL responsibility becomes yours during a crisis like this, whether or not you're entirely to blame. John McCain, and for that matter myself, would never let thousands of Americans die from a pandemic while in office.
